0come%20to%20the%20US%20ahead%20of%20us)%2C%20I%20had%20mixed%20feelings%3A%20I%20could%20feel%20the%20excitement%20of%20my%20eldest%20to%20see%20her%20dad%20again%2C%20but%20I%20also%20feared%20the%20unknown.%20I%20kept%20asking%20myself%20whether%20it%20was%20really%20possible%20that%20we%20could%20fix%20our%20marriage%20and%20thrive%20in%20a%20different%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a036cfd3-9614-4af8-91e1-9f3da896b6bb%5C%22%3EMy%20worst%20fear%20came%20true%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGoing%20from%20living%20in%20a%20penthouse%20in%20the%20old%20part%20of%20Sevilla%2C%20where%20I%20could%20walk%20to%20just%20about%20everywhere%2C%20to%20being%20cooped%20up%20in%20a%20tiny%20apartment%20in%20a%20gated%20community%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffavorite-parts-of-life-in-america-moving-from-england%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esuburban%20Florida%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20I%20needed%20a%20car%20to%20go%20anywhere%2C%20was%20brutal%20to%20my%20nervous%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20felt%20trapped%20in%20suburbia%20without%20my%20own%20car.%20And%20with%20a%20history%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freference%2Fwhat-is-depression%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emajor%20depressive%20disorder%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20started%20having%20panic%20attacks%20and%20depressive%20episodes.%20One%20day%2C%20while%20driving%20my%20children%20to%20find%20a%20preschool%20for%20my%20eldest%2C%20I%20had%20to%20pull%20over%20to%20sob.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20months%20later%2C%20my%20husband%20lost%20the%20job%20we%20had%20moved%20to%20Florida%20for.%20And%20so%20began%20one%20of%20the%20most%20difficult%20periods%20of%20our%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20four%20years%2C%20we%20moved%20several%20times%20within%20Florida%2C%20always%20because%20of%20his%20new%20jobs.%20I%20found%20work%20freelancing%20for%20newspapers%20and%20magazines%20and%20wrote%20more%20books%20for%20publishers%20in%20Spain.%20But%20our%20rel